<Window x:Class="ThirtyOne.GuideWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:ThirtyOne"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="Guide" Background="CornflowerBlue" ResizeMode="NoResize" Height="650" Width="800">
    <Grid>
        <TextBlock FontFamily="Georgia, serif" Padding="3" FontSize="14" Foreground="#FFFBF9F9" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="26,33,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="732" Height="527"><Run Text="1- Rules and calculation:"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="There are ten choices and they are: 12, 11, 10, 9, 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, and Low."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The player can use an option only once during the game."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The calculation for the first nine options is based on the number of combinations corresponding"/><Run Text=" "/><Run Text="to the option multiplied by the option's value."/><Run Text=" Low is a special option where it is calculated by adding up the dices of less than four."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Demonstration for the calculation, after one round, if the player gets the following combination: 5, 1, 6, 2, 3,"/><Run Text=" "/><Run Text="and 4, then one possibility is to choose option 6, and that will give 18 points"/><Run Text=" because the combination of the dices can form three sixes: ({ 5, 1 }, { 6}, { 2, 4 })."/><Run Text=" Another option is 8, which would give"/><Run Text=" 16 points because the combination can form two eights: ({ 5, 3 }, { 6, 2 }). In terms of the Low option, the combination will give only 6 points: (1, 2, 3)."/><Run Text=" Thus, one combination can give different results. In this game, the application will automatically choose for the player the"/><Run Text=" best option available that will give the maximum points."/><Run Text=" Thus, the player will not have to do any calculations to choose the best option;"/><Run Text=" rather, the application will carry out this task."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="2 - How to play:"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The game is played with six dices and it consists of ten rounds where each round consists of three rolls."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Thus, the player will be rolling the dices thirty times in total during one game."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="In the first roll of each round, the player throws all the dices."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Afterward, the player can choose which dice to roll and which dice to keep."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="After each round, the result will be calculated."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The total score is the total number of points that are gained in all ten rounds. "/></TextBlock>

    </Grid>
</Window>
